<%args>
	$err => undef
	$first => undef
	$last => undef
	$email => undef
	$phone => undef
</%args>

	<div class="left huge">

		<h2>Create your tabroom.com account</h2>

		<table cellpadding="5" cellspacing="1" width="97%" style="margin-left: 15px;">  
		
			<tr class="evenrow">

				<td>
					First Name:
				</td>

				<td>
					<form action="new_user_save.mhtml" method="post">
					<input value="<% $first %>" type="text" name="first" size="30">
				</td>

			</tr> 
			
			<tr class="oddrow">
			
				<td>
					Last Name:
				</td>
				
				<td>
					<input value="<% $last %>" type="text" name="last" size="30">
				</td> 

			</tr> 
			
			<tr class="evenrow">
			
				<td>
					Email Address:
				</td>
				
				<td>
					<input value="<% $email %>" type="text" name="email" size="30">
				</td>
				
			</tr> 
			
			<tr class="oddrow">

				<td>
					Phone Number:
				</td>
				
				<td>
					<input value="<% $phone %>" type="text" name="phone" size="30">
				</td>

			</tr> 
			
			<tr class="evenrow">
			
				<td>
					Password:
				</td>
				
				<td>
					<input type="password" name="pass1" size="30">
				</td>
				
			</tr> 
			
			<tr class="oddrow">
			
				<td>
					Repeat the Password:
				</td>
				
				<td>
					<input type="password" name="pass2" size="30">
				</td>
				
			</tr> 
			
			<tr class="liblrow">
				<td colspan="2" align="right">
					<input class="blue" type="submit" value="Create Account">
					</form>
				</td>
			</tr>
			
		</table>

	</div>

	<div id="rightsmall" style="padding-left: 8px; font-size: 95%;">

		<h3>What is tabroom.com?</h3>

		<p>Tabroom.com is a free web based tournament registration & tabulation
		system written by Chris Palmer and managed by him, Jim Menick and
		Charlie Sloat. It is used by hundreds of tournaments annually.  Tabroom
		is a free service to the forensics community made possible by the
		generous support of <a href="http://www.summitdebate.com">Summit
		Debate</a> and <a href="http://www.askonline.net">AskOnline</a>.</p>

		<p>Your tabroom.com account will allow you to register your team for
		tournaments hosted by tabroom.com.  You can also use your tabroom
		account to run your own tournament.</p>

		<p>If you have trouble using tabroom.com, please email
		help@tabroom.com.</p>

		<p>We don't spam or share info, having zero profit motive.  You can
		even turn all email notifications from tabroom itself off.  We'll
		delete any personal information on request</p>


	</div>

